{
  "stem": "3022.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And many of them used to leave Poland for their higher education.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They had-- and it was very well known that the universities of Poland, they had what would be known over here as a Jim Crow line, that the Jews had to sit only in the certain spots.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And as a protest, Jewish students never sat down.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They used to stand in the back of a class.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Through the-- through the four years of their study at the university, Jewish students would never sit down.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They would stand for the four years as a protest, and besides the fact that there were incidents of anti-Semitism and beating by the academia and the exclusion from professions.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In 1938, if I remember correctly, the Polish government issued a-- a law where they barred Jews-- Jewish attorneys from the Bar Association.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They wouldn't admit any more Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They were complaining about the fact that ratio-wise, it-- it was out of proportion.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The amount of-- of Jews in the profession were not in proportion to-- to the amount of Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Jews constituted 10% of the Polish population.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Out of 35 million Poles, about three and a half million were Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We were the second largest minority.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The largest minorities were the Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The second largest minority were the Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The Ukrainians were not as persecuted as Jews because they were a force, and they were all concentrated in one part of the country, in the-- in the southeastern part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But the Jews as a minority were-- were officially and unofficially persecuted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "There-- there were organizations, especially academic organizations, the [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "ED, ?] that-- that seeked exclusion of Jews from the country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They looked to-- to have the Jews forcefully sent out from the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
